    "num": 74,
    "client": "Legion",
    "project": "AI-Powered Financial Intelligence Platform (Personal Project)",
    "about": "Legion is a personal project — an AI-powered financial intelligence platform that scrapes real-time financial news and economic releases from dozens of data sources and passes them through specialist AI agents to deliver hedge fund-grade analysis to retail traders. The platform gives individual traders the equivalent of a full analyst team without requiring millions in capital for institutional-grade portfolio management.",
    "challenge": "Retail traders lack access to the real-time, multi-lens analytical coverage that hedge funds and asset managers rely on. Institutional teams have dedicated risk officers, sovereign analysts, macro analysts and more — each watching the same data through different lenses. Individual traders can't replicate this, leaving them exposed to risks they don't see coming and unable to act on economic events fast enough to protect or optimise their positions.",
    "solution": "I built the entire legion\nai system, hand-coding all frontend and backend components. I designed the entire platform architecture, product strategy, and AI agent framework from the ground up. I conducted interviews with asset management and hedge fund analysts — certified professionals working in risk, sovereign analysis, and macro strategy — to understand how they interpret data and make decisions. I used these insights to design the prompt engineering for each specialist AI agent.\n\nI collated dozens of real-time financial news and economic release data sources into curated publishing feeds. The platform uses a pub/sub architecture where these feeds act as publishers and specialist AI agents act as subscribers. Users subscribe their agents to specific feeds relevant to their portfolio. Each agent analyses data through a different lens — a risk officer agent, a sovereign analyst agent, a macro analyst agent, and others — mirroring how institutional analyst teams operate. The multi-agent ensemble approach, where the same data is analysed through multiple specialist perspectives, prevents overfitting and guards against rogue hallucinations affecting trading decisions.\n\nI designed a two-layer LLM processing pipeline to optimise cost: a cheaper model handles the first layer, performing simple classification of whether incoming data is relevant to the user's portfolio, while a more capable model handles the second layer — generating actionable insights on whether a position's risk should be reduced. This keeps credit usage efficient without sacrificing quality on the analysis that matters.\n\nI also designed API connections so users can integrate Legion's outputs directly into their own automated trading strategies.",
