    "solution": "The custom LLM was a waste of time — this was a straightforward document parsing task that an off-the-shelf model handles perfectly well. I built a quick prototype using a standard model, demo'd it to the team, and showed them it worked. After that they essentially took my code and copied it straight into the application.\n\nThe bigger challenge was the client relationship. I reviewed all the designs and wireframes from scratch and found the original designs weren't fit for purpose. I rebuilt them, and also created a knowledge base MCP with ASM documentation so the team could verify declarations were being sent through correctly — giving them a reliable reference for the complex customs data formats rather than guessing or constantly asking.\n\nOnce everything was documented properly and everyone was on the same page through updated wireframes and accessible documentation, delivery went very smoothly. We initially promised only 2 declaration types but ended up delivering 5 — completely overdelivering on what had been a project the client was about to take legal action over.",
