    "about": "FYIO is a secure digital filing cabinet that lets individuals and businesses organise, store, and share important documents. The platform offers deadline tracking, renewal reminders, encrypted document sharing between users, and ID verification — all built on bank-grade AES 256 encryption.",
    "challenge": "FYIO's previous development team had failed to deliver a working product — the app had no coherent designs, the build was incomplete, and the existing codebase wasn't salvageable. The company needed to start again with a proper design foundation and full rebuild to get a product they could actually launch.",
    "solution": "I came in to rescue a project that had stalled under previous developers. There were no designs, no design system, and no clear UX — just incomplete code that wasn't fit for purpose.\n\nI started with business analysis to understand the full scope of what FYIO needed to be: a personal document vault, a business document management tool, and an enterprise platform for secure document exchange — three distinct user types with different workflows. I mapped out the information architecture and user journeys for each tier, then moved into wireframing and UX design for the complete platform.\n\nThe core design challenge was making document management feel simple when the underlying functionality is quite complex — encrypted sharing between users with automatic filing on the recipient's end, deadline tracking across different document types with different renewal cycles, and ID verification flows for the enterprise tier. I designed and hand-coded the prototype for the filing system to feel as intuitive as a physical filing cabinet while supporting the kind of sharing and automation that only works digitally. The rebuild was developed from my wireframes and specifications, giving the team a clear blueprint that the previous engagement had lacked entirely. The project went from stalled and unshippable to a fully designed product ready for development — turning what had been wasted investment into a viable launch. Since relaunching, the app has gained approximately 2,000 downloads and 1,500 sign-ups.",
