    "solution": "I led the solution design for a lift-and-shift rebuild of the Transparency portal, scoped to retain all existing functionality while giving UCAN full ownership and a platform they can extend.\n\nThe current portal covers a broad feature set across six areas: agency management (offices, agencies, onboarding, Merit ID and Zoho ID integration), reporting and data (live payroll dashboards, evidence views, data exports, timesheets), payments (held payments overview, global payment settings, HMRC payment marking, payment breakdowns), user management (roles, users, responsibilities), a form and table builder for custom fields and columns, email templates, and a Snowflake integration feeding the data layer.\n\nThe rebuild maintains the Snowflake connection and preserves the workflows that 300 agencies already depend on, while giving UCAN the technical foundation to add new features driven by the incoming HMRC shared liability requirements. The architecture is hand-coded the prototype for the so that compliance features can be layered on without disrupting the existing portal experience — agencies need continuity while UCAN needs the flexibility to respond to regulatory changes quickly, which was exactly what their previous provider couldn't offer.",
