    "num": 88,
    "client": "The Fundraising Accountant",
    "project": "",
    "about": "The Fundraising Accountant is a membership community for nonprofit professionals — executive directors, development leaders, accountants, and fractional CFOs. They help nonprofits connect financial data to impact narratives and build sustainable funding strategies through live teaching sessions, working groups, templates, and peer support.",
    "challenge": "The team was running numerous meetings with prospects and members but the post-meeting workflow was entirely manual. After every call, someone had to download the Teams transcript, paste it into ChatGPT to generate a recap, then manually file the output into HubSpot against the correct organisation. For existing members, they also maintained a 'member journey' document — a continuously evolving narrative of that organisation's progress — which required manually updating after each interaction. This process consumed significant time and was inconsistently followed.",
    "solution": "Managing this engagement with a US-based client meant working across time zones and adapting to how American nonprofit communities operate — their expectations around member experience and data handling differ from UK norms, so I invested time upfront understanding their world before jumping into solution design.\n\nI designed and hand-coded the prototype for an automated pipeline that eliminates the entire manual post-meeting workflow. A Power Automate script monitors Teams and grabs completed meeting transcripts, saving them into a staging folder. From there, the system reads each transcript to identify participants, then matches them against HubSpot to find the associated organisations.\n\nThe next step determines whether the organisation is a prospect or an existing member — this distinction drives what happens next. For every meeting, the system generates a structured recap. For existing members, it also updates their member journey document — that continuously evolving narrative of the organisation's engagement and progress. The LLM reads the existing journey document and the new transcript, then produces an updated version that weaves in the latest interaction rather than just appending notes. This keeps the document coherent as a story rather than a log.\n\nAll generated documents — recaps and updated journey narratives — are saved back into HubSpot against the correct organisation record automatically. What used to be a manual process of downloading, prompting ChatGPT, copying, and filing per meeting now happens without any human intervention. The team reclaimed hours of admin time per week that had been spent on post-meeting busywork, and the member journey documents became consistently maintained rather than sporadically updated when someone remembered.",
