    "solution": "I built the working prototype for the platform, designing and implementing the core experience: the player database interface, stat sheet visualisations with percentile rankings, the filtering and discovery workflows, and the AI-powered search that lets scouts describe what they're looking for in natural football language rather than constructing database queries.\n\nWhen the development team took over and implemented the LLM search layer, it wasn't returning accurate results. They'd used pure semantic search, which works well for conceptual queries but struggles with exact data matching — if a scout searches for a specific player name, league, or stat threshold, semantic similarity alone misses or misranks results. I rebuilt the search as a hybrid system combining exact string matching with semantic search. The exact match layer handles names, clubs, leagues, and precise numerical filters, while the semantic layer handles the natural language intent — things like \"quick centre-back comfortable on the ball\" or \"target man who can hold up play.\"\n\nThe platform is built to be accessible to everyone at a club, not just scouts and analysts — coaches, sporting directors, and recruitment teams can all generate tailored one-click reports and collaborate in shared workspaces. The hybrid search fix resolved the accuracy issues that had been undermining confidence in the platform's AI layer, turning it from a tool that missed obvious results into one scouts could rely on for both precise lookups and exploratory discovery.",
