    "challenge": "Machine learning models for trading require vast amounts of data to train effectively, but historical market data is finite and using it for both training and validation leads to overfitting — strategies that perform well on past data but fail in live markets. The core difficulty in generating synthetic financial data is preserving the complex statistical properties that make real markets behave the way they do: cross-instrument correlations, autocorrelation structures, fat-tailed distributions, and volatility clustering. Without these properties, synthetic data is useless for strategy development.",
