    "solution": "I designed and hand-coded a diffusion model-based system for generating synthetic financial time series data. The approach works by learning to gradually add noise to real market data until it becomes pure randomness, then reversing that process — learning to denoise step by step to reconstruct data with realistic statistical properties. This denoising process gives the model a fundamentally different way of capturing market dynamics compared to adversarial approaches.\n\nThe diffusion model learns the full joint distribution of the data including cross-instrument correlations, autocorrelation structures, fat-tailed return distributions, and volatility clustering. By controlling the noise schedule and sampling process, the system generates entirely novel time series that preserve these statistical properties without reproducing any real historical sequences — achieving zero real data contamination.\n\nThis means traders can train their strategies on effectively unlimited synthetic scenarios while reserving all real market data for out-of-sample validation. The system can generate market conditions and tail events that haven't occurred in recorded history, stress-testing strategies against scenarios they'd never encounter in backtesting alone. The diffusion approach also offers finer control over the generation process — you can condition on specific market regimes or volatility levels to generate targeted scenarios for particular strategy weaknesses.\n\nI validated the output against real market data across correlation structures, return distributions, autocorrelation profiles, and tail behaviour to confirm statistical fidelity with no real data leakage. The diffusion approach offers traders a complementary generation method to adversarial techniques, with finer control over targeted scenario generation — enabling more rigorous strategy validation and reducing the risk of overfitting that plagues models trained solely on historical data.",
